---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import avatar from '../assets/avatar.jpg';
import heroPresenting from '../assets/headers/hero-presenting.jpg';
import airiSpeaking from '../assets/headers/airi-speaking.jpg';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Alexander K Saeri — AI governance research"
  description="I direct the MIT AI Risk Initiative, building the evidence base that decision-makers need to manage the most important risks from AI."
>
  <section class="lead-block">
    <h1>Shaping the governance of advanced AI.</h1>
    <p class="lede">I direct the <strong>MIT AI Risk Initiative</strong>, building the evidence base that decision-makers need to manage the most important risks from AI.</p>
    <div class="cta-row">
      <a href="https://airisk.mit.edu" class="btn">Explore the AI Risk Repository</a>
      <a href="#contact" class="btn btn-outline">Request a briefing</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Image
    src={heroPresenting}
    alt="Alexander K Saeri presenting at the EA Global conference, November 2025"
    class="header-banner"
    widths={[600, 1000, 1600]}
    sizes="(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 800px"
    loading="eager"
  />

  <div class="section" id="about">
    <h2>About</h2>
    <div class="profile-header">
      <Image src={avatar} alt="Alexander K Saeri" class="profile-image" widths={[200, 400]} sizes="(max-width: 600px) 200px, 400px" />
      <div class="profile-content">
        <p>I'm a researcher and research leader focused on understanding and managing risks from advanced AI systems. I direct the MIT AI Risk Initiative at MIT FutureTech, and hold positions at MIT FutureTech and the University of Queensland. I'm based in Melbourne.</p>
        <p>My methods background is in social psychology, applied behaviour science, implementation science, systems thinking, and survey research. I am most interested in improving policy and governance for highly capable general-purpose AI.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section" id="airi">
    <h2>MIT AI Risk Initiative</h2>
    <p>I direct the MIT AI Risk Initiative (AIRI), a research project at MIT FutureTech that provides authoritative data and frameworks to help decision-makers across the AI ecosystem identify, prioritise, and manage the most important risks from AI.</p>

    <Image
      src={airiSpeaking}
      alt="Alexander K Saeri speaking at the EA Global conference, November 2025"
      class="header-banner"
      widths={[600, 1000, 1600]}
      sizes="(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 800px"
    />

    <ul class="workstreams">
      <li>
        <div class="workstream-name">AI Risk Repository</div>
        <p class="workstream-q">What are the risks from AI? Which are highest priority?</p>
        <p class="workstream-a">A common taxonomy and database synthesising over 1,700 risks from 74 frameworks, used by governments, standards bodies, and AI labs.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <div class="workstream-name">AI Risk Index</div>
        <p class="workstream-q">How are leading organisations responding to AI risks?</p>
        <p class="workstream-a">An expert prioritisation of risks and an assessment of how key actors across the ecosystem are managing them.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <div class="workstream-name">AI Mitigations Repository</div>
        <p class="workstream-q">What are the mitigations for AI risks? Which are most effective?</p>
        <p class="workstream-a">A structured database of mitigation strategies extracted from frameworks across technical, policy, and governance domains.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <div class="workstream-name">AI Incident Tracking</div>
        <p class="workstream-q">Which real-world harms from AI are already occurring?</p>
        <p class="workstream-a">A collaboration with the AI Incident Database to monitor and analyse documented incidents.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <div class="workstream-name">AI Governance Mapping</div>
        <p class="workstream-q">Which laws and governance approaches cover which risks?</p>
        <p class="workstream-a">A collaboration with the Center for Security and Emerging Technology (CSET) at Georgetown to systematically map governance documents against risk and mitigation taxonomies.</p>
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Impact</h3>
    <p>AIRI's work is widely used and cited. Since launch in 2024, the website has had 250,000+ visits and 180+ academic citations. It is referenced in the <em>International AI Safety Report 2025</em> and Canada's <em>Implementation Guide for Managers of AI Systems</em>, and has been adopted by IBM, Credo AI, the Vector Institute, and the AI Incident Database. The 2024 Repository paper received the most media coverage of any research released by MIT CSAIL across 2024 and 2025.</p>

    <blockquote class="pullquote">
      <p>"The MIT AI Risk Repository is a valuable database for accessing current and comprehensive information on a wide range of AI-related risks. This resource helps fill a critical information gap by bringing more rigor and transparency to AI risk management."</p>
      <footer>Yoshua Bengio, Turing Award winner, Université de Montréal, Founder and Scientific Advisor of Mila</footer>
    </blockquote>
  </div>

  <div class="section" id="ecosystem">
    <h2>Australia's AI safety ecosystem</h2>
    <p>Alongside AIRI, I help build Australia's AI safety ecosystem. I collaborate with <a href="https://www.goodancestors.org.au/safe-and-responsible-ai">Good Ancestors Policy</a> on policy analysis and submissions, convene the <a href="https://aisafety.org.au/project/melbourne/">Melbourne AI safety community</a>, designed and facilitated the inaugural <a href="https://aisafetyforum.au/">Australian AI Safety Forum (2024)</a>, and help maintain <a href="https://aisafety.org.au/">AISafety.org.au</a>.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="section" id="publications">
    <h2>Selected publications</h2>

    <h3>Recent</h3>
    <ul class="publications">
      <li>Slattery, P., <strong>Saeri, A. K.</strong>, Grundy, E. A. C., Graham, J., Noetel, M., Uuk, R., Dao, J., Pour, S., Caspar, S., &amp; Thompson, N. (2024). <em>The AI Risk Repository: A Comprehensive Meta-Review, Database, and Taxonomy of Risks From Artificial Intelligence.</em> arXiv:2408.12622. <a href="https://doi.org/10.48550/arXiv.2408.12622">doi.org/10.48550/arXiv.2408.12622</a></li>
      <li><strong>Saeri, A. K.</strong>, Noetel, M., &amp; Graham, J. (2024). <em>Survey Assessing Risks from Artificial Intelligence: Technical Report.</em> UQ / Ready Research. <a href="https://doi.org/10.2139/ssrn.4750953">doi.org/10.2139/ssrn.4750953</a></li>
      <li><strong>Saeri, A. K.</strong>, &amp; O'Connor, R. M. A. (2023). <em>Applying AI to sustainability policy challenges: A practical playbook.</em> Monash University. <a href="https://doi.org/10.31219/osf.io/y75rq">doi.org/10.31219/osf.io/y75rq</a></li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Earlier</h3>
    <ul class="publications">
      <li><strong>Saeri, A. K.</strong> et al. (2022). <em>What Works to Increase Charitable Donations? A Meta-Review with Meta-Meta-Analysis.</em> VOLUNTAS. <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/s11266-022-00499-y">doi.org/10.1007/s11266-022-00499-y</a></li>
    </ul>

    <p>Full list: <a href="https://scholar.google.com.au/citations?user=B_bJG3kAAAAJ">Google Scholar</a>.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="section" id="contact">
    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>I'm available for advising and speaking on AI governance, risk management, and research-to-policy translation. Get in touch if you'd like to discuss collaboration, a briefing, or an engagement.</p>
    <p>
      <strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:alexander@aksaeri.com">alexander@aksaeri.com</a><br>
      <strong>Phone:</strong> <a href="tel:+61405519733">+61 405 519 733</a>
    </p>
    <div class="cta-row">
      <a href="https://calendar.app.google/sv3Sb5sjUxxTdssv8" class="btn">Schedule a meeting</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
